        "content": "<p>When an existing theorem directly matches a goal, which of the following is preferred?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"...\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">using</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"...\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_theorem</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 523372857,
        "sender_full_name": "Sage Binder",
        "timestamp": 1749590631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I prefer the latter, but that's mostly personal preference.</p>",
        "id": 523496484,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabian Huch",
        "timestamp": 1749627045
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I try to skip those steps...</p>",
        "id": 523517606,
        "sender_full_name": "Mathias Fleury",
        "timestamp": 1749634003
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>note H = my_theorem[of ...]</code> would also work</p>",
        "id": 523517761,
        "sender_full_name": "Mathias Fleury",
        "timestamp": 1749634065
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The rule version has the advantage to have an implicit standard applied, which can be useful to discharge assumptions</p>",
        "id": 523517908,
        "sender_full_name": "Mathias Fleury",
        "timestamp": 1749634113
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's also the \"fact\" method for that sort of thing. Can take a theorem as a parameter, or can figure it out automatically if there's a suitable fact in the context</p>",
        "id": 539992623,
